Visual Calculus: More old bullet holes, at least half a century. A different era altogether.
Pain Threshold: Your chest feels tight, looking at them. It's closing in... caving in, ever tighter. Your breathing grows even heavier.
Kim Kitsuragi: "You okay there?" The lieutenant's sudden voice cuts like a blade, bringing you out of the stupor.
You: "Man, I started feeling really bad for a second."
Shivers: The streets ran red with blood. Dust swirled above the ruins. The pressure change from artillery fire ripped people apart in the top floors of the building above you...
You: "These bullet holes look like the bullet holes we saw before."
